beer.beer_description: Witbier meaning ‘white beer’ in Flemish, is a medieval style of beer from Belgium that was revived in the 1960s. This pale hazy wheat beer is brewed with coriander and orange peel. Whiter shades of ale has a full bodied mouthfeel from the large amount of wheat and oats used. Yet still highly refreshing with its carbonation, a dry finish and low bitterness.
